If someone is making a difficult life decision, there are several ways I can support them.

First, I can listen to them without judgment, allowing them to express their thoughts and feelings. Sometimes, all people need is someone to hear them out and understand what they are going through. I can offer a neutral perspective, free from our own biases and emotions, and help them to identify their own strengths and weaknesses.

